caption.body: Not all Talking boards look alike. The Ziriya Creative Arts Corp. produced the Ziriya Human Battery Circuit Talking Board in 1972. This psychedelic-looking board displays words to form sentences, rather than individual letters. The outermost circle reads: "Ziriya will be what you want to be Always respect Ziriya Allow time for Ziriya to warm up Be patient Avoid distractions and disturbances while operating Do not interrupt a message Concentrate on the question and answer  Think positively If you are fatigued while operating messages may have no meaning"  All objects are courtesy of Gene Orlando, Museum of Talking Boards, and Robert Murch, The Talking Board Historical Society. See more spooky #OuijaBoards in "The Mysterious Talking Board: #OuijaAndBeyond" on display, post-security, in Terminal 2. http://bit.ly/OuijaAndBeyond #OuijaBoard #TalkingBoard  G O O D B Y E
